{"parts":[{"tool_name":"tool_docs","content":"Send an email to the user's email address.
If the user has connected their Gmail account, another way to send email is using the Gmail tool. However, this tool is the simplest and recommended way to send an email to the user.

Args:
    subject: Email subject line (required, non-empty).
    markdown_body: Email body in Markdown (required unless attachments are provided).
    attachments: Optional list of absolute file paths to attach (total size <= 10MB).","tool_call_id":"tool_docs:0","metadata":null,"timestamp":"2026-02-07T01:23:13.686881Z","part_kind":"tool-return"},{"tool_name":"run_bash_command","content":{"stdout":"{
  "queries": [
    {
      "name": "tagged_from_shivam",
      "query": "from:shivam@corridorx.io (subject:[JD] OR subject:[RESUME] OR subject:[UPDATE]) is:unread",
      "priority": 1
    },
    {
      "name": "untagged_from_shivam",
      "query": "from:shivam@corridorx.io -subject:[JD] -subject:[RESUME] -subject:[UPDATE] is:unread newer_than:1d",
      "priority": 2
    }
  ],
  "instructions": "Use gmail-find-email with each query string"
}
